Political Capital: Hungarian Guard increases State risk
According to the Risk Analysis Division of Political Capital, the activities of the Hungarian Guard, established this August with the support of the "Movement for a Better Hungary," have increased the risk of Hungary and the region in several respects.
The Institute's "risk-warning report" states, among other things, that in the context of the activities of the Hungarian Guard, the highest political risk is "the strengthening of the existing ethnic tensions between the Gypsies and non-Gypsies in Hungary, which could even lead to violent ethnic conflicts in the short term."
The main reason for this was the strategy of the Hungarian Guard, which is probably aimed at provocation of such an argument, according to the research institute.
As reported, this is seen as a failure by the political leaders: "People of public life have left the discussion of the Roma issue to representatives of radical political groups who have now built their political strategy on the Roma-Hungary opposition."
It is assumed that this would exacerbate the problem, make it impossible for reasonable dialogue, promote extremities, and increase the likelihood of violent conflicts.
The research institute also believes that the activities of the Hungarian Guard, not least thanks to the huge attention of the domestic and foreign media, "have seriously damaged the image of Hungary abroad, in particular as regards confidence in stability and democratic maturity."
We remember: Since autumn 2006, the reorganisation of radical and extremely right-wing groups in Hungary has been in the upswing, so since summer 2007 several "national self-defence association" have been established.
"These groups are common in their definition of themselves as civil organizations, while they openly boast of preparing their members for - sometimes armed - defence tasks (civil protection, state defense, order prevention), calling for the inadequacy of the police, the army, or the state itself," it was said.
And further, all of this is done in accordance with the method that is trying to disguise various political aspirations based on the political and party defiance of the population as a bourgeois initiative.
The emphasis on the civil character and the form of the association is not only to avoid legal obstacles that could arise in the course of the registration of the court - it is also a political strategy.
As the analysis shows, the activities of the Hungarian Guard are also a risk-increasing factor for relations with neighbouring countries.
"In recent months, the Hungarian Guard has been cited as a potential source of danger in several neighbouring countries, as some ultranationalist politicians of certain neighbouring countries see the emergence of the Hungarian Guard as the confirmation of its own anti-Hungary policy.
All this has an impact on the political stability of the region "- it said.
From the point of view of the research institute, the establishment of the Hungarian Guard is not a single phenomenon in Central-East Europe, so the political risk for the whole region has grown.
