The Congress agrees with the MIFID directive, which entered into force on 1 November.
In parallel with the parliamentary preparation, which today ended its meeting with the Congress decision in the Senate on the supplementary / amendment requests related to the project, the government published the provisions of the new law, with the intention of allowing the entry into force of both regulations by the end of the year.
The representatives of the various companies unanimously praised the efforts of the Congressmen and Senate members, who had in their negotiations and votes the aim of establishing the best possible rules to ensure the security of investors and to regulate individual business activities in order to guarantee a generally efficient market operation.
In addition to the modernisation of the financial markets, the MIFID, which redefines the Investment Services Regulation, is pursuing an improvement in investor protection, an increase in the control claim of the Spanish Securities Commission (CNMV) and the promotion of cooperation between the various control authorities of the European Union.
The new Directive allows for the provision of financial advice to both specialised companies and to natural or legal persons and also contributes to the creation of new financial services companies (ESIS), the advisory companies that are linked to the investment and brokering companies of securities.
It also extends the number of systems for the execution of financial transactions, so that the regulated circulation markets are added to the multilateral systems of the securities business and to the systems for the internationalisation of trade contracts, which would eventually compete with the current economic operators.
The law obliges the investment companies to make known the priorities of their business profile, the confrontation and the ways in which they deal with risks on the market and to register all the projects carried out in order to facilitate the control of the CNMV.
The Economic Commission of the Congress provided for further amendments in retrospect, with the decision that, due to its high level of risk, the debt bond with the title must now be considered as complex financial resources for the investor being confirmed by the US mortgage and banking crisis. (US mortgage crisis)
In addition, the entry into force of the Directive on the legal limitation of the working areas of qualified economists was used; 30 years after 1977, the Regulation, which restricted the areas reserved for economists, was adopted.
The Senate, for its part, established new positions in the financial sector, such as that of the economic mediator, who works on a foreign account, does not need authorisation from the CNMV and can offer its services for the commercialisation of products and for the purchase of customers at the same time several investment companies.
