Which insurance is best for me?
The KFZ insurance, which covers a possible damage caused by the driver, includes a high cost, the amount of which is again dependent on various factors, including age, sex, time of production of the driving licence, family status, type of car to be insured and its use, etc.
Owning a car is just the beginning.
Because it is even more difficult to find the right KFZ insurance than the right vehicle model.
First of all, one must be clear about what we are dealing with here.
A car insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and an insurance undertaking.
This agreement shall be recorded in writing by means of an insurance contract which provides that the company shall receive the insurance premium and in return shall be obliged to provide the corresponding amount of the payment in the event of a damage.
The insurance premium is the price of an insurance which is made up of several factors, including age, sex, date of production of the driving licence, family status, type of vehicle to be insured or use thereof.
Insurance undertakings shall set their prices in accordance with the statistics, so that higher contributions are due in the event of a higher risk of accidents.
For this reason, both 25-year-olds and women have to pay less contributions, as statistics show that these groups have a lower accident rate due to their caution.
The same applies to married persons, as according to the statistical values and therefore to the companies, they tend to be less accidents than single persons.
The benefit of the vehicle is to affect the frequency of driving and therefore the probability of an accident.
The more frequent the use, the more likely the damage.
In drawing up the premium, insurance must take into account a number of points.
For this reason, the driver must also study the situation thoroughly in order to select exactly the car insurance that is most likely to meet his personal needs.
We now list the most important points that should be considered in the selection of insurance in order to be able to make not only a performance but also a price-oriented choice.
The under-25-year-olds encounter numerous obstacles in the choice of low-cost insurance, such as low driving practice and young driving licences.
Even if it would be best for an ideal insurance cover to complete a full-scale insurance, there are still more cost-effective alternatives.
The careful drivers can choose a full-time self-employed, so that the services of a full-scale insurance are covered, but are offered at a low price.
This type of contract implies that the customer must pay part of the amount of the damage itself.
The amount is fixed before the contract is concluded and on the basis of the amount of the insurance premium, which is higher than the amount to be paid, explains Luis Noguera, Spain's main representative at First Europe, a brokerage company for online insurance.
Another option is the extended insurance, which assures the customer against external accident damage, but not against the damage caused by the car itself.
In addition, this type of insurance would cover theft, fire and vehicle loss.
Here's some advice.
If you are under 25, it is in your hand to reduce the insurance costs; so your credit increases by trying to drive and avoid accidents.
A credit is a reduction in the basic rate of the insurance company.
On the contrary, a penalty payment includes an increase in the said rates.
The amount of credits and penalty payments depends on the company and its income.
If the company has a rich year behind it, it can allow itself to increase the bonus payments, explained Noguera.
Once the 25-year mark is exceeded, it is easier for the drivers to conclude a contract. The reason for this is the fact that with increasing driving practice the accident rate decreases.
It is therefore most appropriate to choose a full-scale insurance with self-participation.
Usually, young people cannot benefit from their experience, both in the event of an accident and at the time of driving, as the Spanish head of the European company explains, and adds that the majority of accidents take place in the second year of practice after the fear of the beginner has been lost.
However, it is more advisable for a married customer who does not have children to make full-scale insurance; of course, only if it allows the financial situation of the person concerned.
On the part of the insurers, married couples with children are considered to be the customers with the lowest accident rate and their contributions are therefore low.
In this case, a full-scale self-contribution insurance (with an amount of EUR 300) would be the best option. In the event that you have received a high credit, an extended insurance, which is only used for the third year of the vehicle, is recommended.
They drive more relaxed overall and have a greater purchasing power that allows them to make a higher contribution, Luis Noguera notes.
For pensioners, it is appropriate to conclude a full-scale self-contribution insurance (for an amount of 150 euro) or an extended insurance which only uses a sufficiently high credit.
In the end, it must be noted that car insurance is something very important, not only because it protects the driver from possible accident damage, but also because it has high costs that require a thorough selection that is in line with our personal situation.
